00:00:05.830 --> 00:00:13.330
The following video addresses how to replace the RPWF water filter on your GE bottom freezer refrigerator.

00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:15.960
The filter should be replaced
every six months,

00:00:15.960 --> 00:00:20.539
or earlier if the flow of water to the
dispenser or ice maker decreases.

00:00:20.940 --> 00:00:24.220
Please Note: There is no need to shut
off the water in your house before

00:00:24.220 --> 00:00:25.689
replacing the filter.

00:00:26.140 --> 00:00:30.040
To locate your water filter, open the
left-hand fresh food door

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:34.820
and press the indent at the bottom of the
great panel to allow access to the water filter.

00:00:35.020 --> 00:00:40.450
Gently tilt the RPWF water filter to
approximately 45 degrees.

00:00:40.450 --> 00:00:45.470
Once at 45 degrees. the filter can be
removed by pulling towards you.

00:00:46.260 --> 00:00:48.480
A small amount of water may drip out.

00:00:48.990 --> 00:00:54.160
To reinstall the RPWF filter, align
the notches at the top of the filter

00:00:54.160 --> 00:00:55.700
with the filter head.

00:00:58.969 --> 00:01:02.909
Press in towards the door with the new
are RPWF filter.

00:01:03.140 --> 00:01:05.620
Once firmly seated in the filter
head,

00:01:05.630 --> 00:01:09.000
push down on the body of the water filter.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:11.060
DO NOT twist the filter

00:01:11.990 --> 00:01:16.329
Once the new filter is installed, run
approximately two gallons of water from

00:01:16.329 --> 00:01:19.349
the dispenser to clear the system any air.

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:22.580
Next, reset the filter status.

00:01:24.149 --> 00:01:29.449
On touch-screen models, select the water
filter menu and press the reset button.

00:01:37.410 --> 00:01:39.329
On non touch-screen models,

00:01:39.329 --> 00:01:43.609
press and hold the reset filter button
for three seconds.

00:01:47.950 --> 00:01:50.690
To order replacement parts for your GE appliances, please visit:

00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:54.560
geapplianceparts.com

